*****cls v1.2*****

Usage: cls [ --help | --show | --version | directories]

--Arguments--

--help, -h -	Get all the required help to use cls.

--show, -s -	Get short information about cls currently installed on your system.

--version, -v -	Get release version info of cls currently installed on your system.

directries -	Directories names to list using cls.


Example:

cls

cls -l

cls -lahF

cls testdir1/ testdir2

cls -lahF testdir1/ testdir2

**********
